{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"OESA-2024-2553","published":"2024-12-13T13:18:57Z","modified":"2025-09-03T06:20:19.323790Z","upstream":["CVE-2024-35368","CVE-2024-36616"],"summary":"ffmpeg security update","details":"FFmpeg is a complete and free Internet live audio and video broadcasting solution for Linux/Unix. It also includes a digital VCR. It can encode in real time in many formats including MPEG1 audio and video, MPEG4, h263, ac3, asf, avi, real, mjpeg, and flash.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\r\n\r\nFFmpeg n7.0 is affected by a Double Free via the rkmpp_retrieve_frame function within libavcodec/rkmppdec.c.(CVE-2024-35368)\r\n\r\nAn integer overflow in the component /libavformat/westwood_vqa.c of FFmpeg n6.1.1 allows attackers to cause a denial of service in the application via a crafted VQA file.(CVE-2024-36616)","affected":[{"package":{"name":"ffmpeg","ecosystem":"openEuler:24.03-LTS","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/ffmpeg&distro=openEuler-24.03-LTS"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"6.1.1-16.oe2403"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["ffmpeg-6.1.1-16.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","ffmpeg-debuginfo-6.1.1-16.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","ffmpeg-debugsource-6.1.1-16.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","ffmpeg-devel-6.1.1-16.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","ffmpeg-libs-6.1.1-16.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","libavdevice-6.1.1-16.oe2403.aarch64.rpm"],"src":["ffmpeg-6.1.1-16.oe2403.src.rpm"],"x86_64":["ffmpeg-6.1.1-16.oe2403.x86_64.rpm","ffmpeg-debuginfo-6.1.1-16.oe2403.x86_64.rpm","ffmpeg-debugsource-6.1.1-16.oe2403.x86_64.rpm","ffmpeg-devel-6.1.1-16.oe2403.x86_64.rpm","ffmpeg-libs-6.1.1-16.oe2403.x86_64.rpm","libavdevice-6.1.1-16.oe2403.x86_64.rpm"]},"database_specific":{"source":"https://repo.openeuler.org/security/data/osv/OESA-2024-2553.json"}}],"references":[{"type":"ADVISORY","url":"https://www.openeuler.org/zh/security/security-bulletins/detail/?id=openEuler-SA-2024-2553"},{"type":"ADVISORY","url":"https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2024-35368"},{"type":"ADVISORY","url":"https://nvd